  "text": "The minimal GCC GIMPLE optimization pass implementation follows the established patterns found in the GCC codebase, particularly drawing from tree-ssa-dce.cc and gimple-laddress.cc as primary references. The implementation demonstrates the four key components of a GCC GIMPLE pass: (1) the pass_data struct that holds metadata about the pass including type (GIMPLE_PASS), name, optimization group flags, and properties; (2) a class that inherits from gimple_opt_pass (defined in gcc/tree-pass.h) which is itself derived from opt_pass; (3) virtual method implementations for gate() which determines if the pass should run and execute() which contains the pass logic; and (4) a factory function (make_pass_bb_count) that creates and returns a new instance of the pass. The execute method iterates over all basic blocks in a function using the FOR_EACH_BB_FN macro from gcc/basic-block.h, counting them and reporting the result to the dump_file for debugging output. This pattern is consistent across all GCC GIMPLE passes including the Dead Code Elimination pass (pass_dce) in gcc/tree-ssa-dce.cc and the Lower Address pass (pass_laddress) in gcc/gimple-laddress.cc. The pass integrates into GCC's optimization pipeline by being registered in gcc/passes.def and can be invoked during compilation with appropriate -fdump-tree flags."
